"Well, there seems to me to be only one possible solution. Mr. Rucastle seemed to be a very kind,
good-natured man. Is it not possible that his wife is a lunatic, that he desires to keep the matter
quiet for fear she should be taken to an asylum, and that he humours her fancies in every way in
order to prevent an outbreak?"

"That is a possible solution--in fact, as matters stand, it is the most probable one. But in any
case it does not seem to be a nice household for a young lady."

"But the money, Mr. Holmes, the money!"